messages.content: is air canada part of one world alliance
No, Air Canada is not part of the oneworld alliance. It is a member of the Star Alliance, which is another major global airline alliance.
is the united states a part of the european union
No, the United States is not a part of the European Union. The EU is a political and economic union of European countries. The United States is a separate sovereign nation in North America.
is israel part of the european economic area

No, Israel is not part of the European Economic Area (EEA). The EEA includes member states of the European Union (EU) as well as three of the four European Free Trade Association (EFTA) countries: Norway, Iceland, and Liechtenstein. Israel has its own trade agreements with the EU but is not a member of the EEA.
does university of tampa have a football team

The University of Tampa does not currently have an intercollegiate football team. The university once had a football team, but it was discontinued in the early 1970s. are all the angles equal in a parallelogram

No, not all angles in a parallelogram are necessarily equal. In a parallelogram, opposite angles are equal, but consecutive angles are supplementary (meaning they add up to 180 degrees). 

For a parallelogram to have all four angles equal, it must be a rectangle, which is a specific type of parallelogram where each angle is 90 degrees. In general, though, a parallelogram does not have all angles equal unless it is a rectangle.
is st augustine the oldest city in florida

Yes, St. Augustine is the oldest city in Florida. It was founded by Spanish explorers on September 8, 1565, making it the oldest continuously inhabited European-established settlement in the continental United States. Its rich history and well-preserved architecture make it a popular destination for those interested in the early history of European exploration in North America.

is baylor and mary hardin baylor the same school

No, Baylor University and the University of Mary Hardin-Baylor are not the same school. 

- **Baylor University** is a private Christian university located in Waco, Texas. It is one of the largest Baptist universities in the world and offers a wide range of undergraduate and graduate programs.

- **University of Mary Hardin-Baylor** (UMHB) is a separate institution also affiliated with the Baptist tradition, located in Belton, Texas. UMHB is known for its focus on undergraduate education and offers various bachelor's, master's, and doctoral programs.

While both are Christian institutions with Baptist affiliations, they are distinct and independent universities.
was egypt a part of the ottoman empire

Yes, Egypt was part of the Ottoman Empire. It was officially incorporated into the empire in 1517 after being conquered by the Ottoman sultan Selim I. Although Egypt remained under nominal Ottoman control for centuries, it often enjoyed a degree of autonomy, especially during the rule of Muhammad Ali Pasha in the early 19th century. His descendants ruled Egypt as khedives under Ottoman suzerainty until the British occupation in 1882. The formal end of Ottoman suzerainty came with the British declaration of a protectorate over Egypt in 1914 during World War I.
is tea tree oil and melaluca the same

Yes, tea tree oil and melaleuca refer to the same product. Tea tree oil is an essential oil derived from the leaves of the Melaleuca alternifolia, a tree native to Australia. Often, it is labeled as "melaleuca oil" in various products. This oil is known for its antiseptic, antifungal, and anti-inflammatory properties and is commonly used in skincare, hair care, and natural remedies.
